IP Address:	
Solaris	
find ip address of the server u loggedin	    /usr/sbin/ifconfig -a
find ip address 	                            /usr/sbin/nslookup "server name"

Linux	
find ip of the server u logged in	hostname -i or cat /etc/hosts
------------
Tarring	
normal tarring	tar  -cvf output.tar sourefoldername
gtar	/usr/sfw/bin/gtar cvf
zipping	zip -r fortify-src.zip *
	
Untarring	
normal	tar -xvf filename
gtar	/usr/sfw/bin/gtar xvf
	
FIND	
find a file	find . -name "filename"
particular word in all files	find . -type f|xargs grep -i"word"
	
Soft link	ln -s 'source' linkname 
	
Disk Usage	
	du -sh *
	df -k .
	du -sk *
	du -h -s *(size of subdirectories in a directory)
	du -sh "foldername" -- give the size of a folder
	sf1-3haleqa2-idb-gd $ df -hk /logs
Filesystem             size   used  avail capacity  Mounted on
/dev/dsk/c0d1s0     118G    26G    91G    22%    /logs

Memory Usage	
	vmstat 1 10
	
Port	
To know if a port is listening or free	[netstat -an|grep 'portnumber' |grep LISTEN ]
	
remote host is response	[ping -a "hostname" or "ipaddress"]

export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH
Cat /dev/null > filename  #to empty a file
dircmp -ds -w 100 "directory1" "directory2"	#compare two directories
tail -100f "log file name" |grep ""
tail -100f access.log | awk '{print $8}'
cat filename | sort -u  #sorts and displays only unique
fgrep -x -f file1 file2  #displays common thing in both files
fgrep -v -f file1 file2 #displays the things in file2 which are not there in file1
/opt/apps/java/jdk180_131SV/bin/keytool -list -v -keystore “JKS file”

find . -type f -exec grep  -l tapapp_2015.02.0 {} + [find the file names which has particular word]
find . -type f | xargs grep -c tapapp_2015.02.0 | grep -v ":0" [find the file names which has particular word]

